@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    /* Reusing the color variables and base styles for consistency */
    :root {
        --primary-color: #6a11cb;
        --secondary-color: #2575fc;
        --background-color: #121212;
        --surface-color: #1e1e1e;
        --text-color: #e0e0e0;
        --text-muted-color: #888;
    }

    /* Hero Section Styling */
    .hero-section {
        padding: 4rem 0;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .hero-section h1 {
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--primary-color), var(--secondary-color));
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .hero-section .subtitle {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: var(--text-muted-color);
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    /* Content styling for the policy */
    .privacy-content {
        background-color: var(--surface-color);
        padding: 2.5rem;
        border-radius: 12px;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        text-align: left;
        line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .privacy-content h2 {
        color: var(--secondary-color);
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #444;
    }
    
    .privacy-content h2:first-of-type {
        margin-top: 0;
    }

    .privacy-content p {
        color: var(--text-muted-color);
    }
    
    .privacy-content ul {
        color: var(--text-muted-color);
        padding-left: 20px;
    }
    
    .privacy-content a {
        color: var(--secondary-color);
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .privacy-content a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

</style>

<!-- Page Header -->
<section class="hero-section">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Your trust is important to us. Here's how we protect your data.</p>
</section>

<!-- Main Privacy Policy Content -->
<div class="privacy-content">
    

    <p>Welcome to LinkShortener. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our website and services. By using our service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>To provide our link shortening and analytics services, we collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Original URL:</strong> The long URL that you wish to shorten.</li>
        <li><strong>Generated Short URL:</strong> The shortened link we create for you.</li>
        <li><strong>Click Data:</strong> When a short link is clicked, we automatically collect certain information, including:
            <ul>
                <li><strong>IP Address:</strong> To help prevent spam and identify general geographic locations (note: we do not currently display this information).</li>
                <li><strong>Referrer Information:</strong> The website that linked to our short URL (e.g., "google.com", "facebook.com", or "Direct" if no referrer is available).</li>
                <li><strong>Date and Time:</strong> The timestamp of each click.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>To Provide and Maintain Our Service:</strong> To create short links, redirect users to the original URL, and ensure the service is functioning correctly.</li>
        <li><strong>To Provide Analytics:</strong> To display click statistics for your short links, including total clicks, referrers, and clicks over time.</li>
        <li><strong>To Improve and Secure Our Service:</strong> To monitor for malicious activity, prevent abuse, and understand usage patterns to improve our platform.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p><strong>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personally identifiable information to outside parties.</strong> The analytics data for a specific short link is only visible on the "Track URL Clicks" page and is only displayed when that specific short link is entered.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We store the link data (original URL, short URL, and associated click data) indefinitely to ensure that your short links continue to function and that analytics remain available. If you wish for a specific link and its data to be deleted, please contact us.</p>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to request access to or deletion of your link data. Please contact us with your request, and we will respond in a timely manner.</p>
    
    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:</p>
    <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@yourdomain.com">linkshortener11@gmail.com</a></p>
</div>
